<p>Thiruvananthapuram, probably better known, simply as Trivandrum, is a city that has many popular temples and museums, making it one of the best artistic and cultural centers of Kerala. The very mention of Trivandrum will conjure images of pagoda-shaped buildings, winding lanes and the red-tiled roofs. In the case of Trivandrum, the city will actually live up to your expectations and it is this peculiar old-world charm that gives the city its great tourist appeal.</p><p>The city of Trivandrum has a sublime tropical climate as it is located along the Arabian Sea. It also has a gorgeous shoreline, with beautiful beaches that are certainly worth a visit, Kovalam being one of the popular. The beaches are popular with locals and tourists alike and will offer the perfect opportunity to relax and vegetate or enjoy water sports and learn surf-boarding.</p><p><a href="https://www.cleartrip.com/tourism/airports/trivandrum-airport.html" target="_blank">Trivandrum International Airport</a> connects the city with the rest of the country and the world. The airport is located at a distance of 3.7 km from the center of the city and roughly 13 km from Technopark. The airport has two terminals, with terminal 1 catering to domestic flights, and terminal 2 catering to international flights.</p><p>Traveling to and from the airport is easy and convenient, as the airport is at an optimum distance from most important hubs of the city. The city bus stand is located at a distance of 6 km and Trivandrum railway station at about 4 km from the airport. Pre-paid taxis are also easily available in the city.</p><p>If you are traveling during the months of June and July make it a point to set out for the airport early and always keep track of flight information, as heavy rainfall can cause traffic and flight delays.</p>